import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = data.boxplot(column='Beak_Length__mm_', by='Species')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of beak length across different species of penguins?")
    plt.suptitle("")
    plt.xlabel("Species")
    plt.ylabel("Beak Length (mm)")
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data.groupby('Sex')['Body_Mass__g_'].plot.hist(alpha=0.5, legend=True)
    plt.xlabel('Body Mass (g)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('How does the body mass of male and female penguins compare?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
